To implement a customer feedback system, basic steps include: 
1. Set objectives for collecting customer feedback; 
2. Determine the methods, channels and frequency of customer feedback collection;
3. Design customer feedback forms and surveys;
4. Develop customer feedback reporting, analysis and communication systems;
5. Test and launch the customer feedback system;
6. Monitor and adjust the system as needed;
7. Track customer feedback and take action accordingly.
